s0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fession on record for our instruction. Daniel (Dan. 9:3-2o), </div><div class="t m5fd x18 he y1553 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ezra (Ezra 9 : 5 ; to : t), and David (Ps. 51 :1-4) are familiar </div><div class="t mb6c x26 he y10eb ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cases. &quot;True confession is always of a specific character, </div><div class="t m39c x26 he y135b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and acknowledges particular sins.&quot; &quot;Confession will not </div><div class="t m7ca x18 he y1e0b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be acceptable to God without sincere repentance and ref-</div><div class="t m4a3 x26 he yc7e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ormation.&quot; &quot;Whatever the character of your sin, confess, </div><div class="t m1384 xaa he yc7e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m261 x18 he y1b34 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">it. </div><div class="t m5 x48 he y1b34 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1468 x28 he y1b34 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">If it is against God only, confess only to him. If you </div><div class="t m612 x18 he yeaa ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">have wronged or offended others, confess also to them, and </div><div class="t ma70 x18 he y74c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the blessing of the Lord will rest upon you.&quot; &quot;Sins that </div><div class="t m8a0 x18 he y1ed3 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are not confessed will never be forgiven.&quot; </div><div class="t m1ab x74 he yeac ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Our past sins will sometimes come to mind and cast a </div><div class="t mb15 x18 he y1cca ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">shadow over our faith, so that we can see nothing but mer- </div><div class="t m2c3 x18 he y1dc4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ited punishment in store for us. But at such times, while </div><div class="t m5a1 x4a he yf4c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">we feel sorrow for sins, we should look to Jesus, and be-</div><div class="t mf22 x4a he y11b7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lieve that he has pardoned our transgressions.&quot; &quot; If you <